--- body ---
## Problem

`housekeeping_needed()` in beat.py only checks if the last housekeeping commit is
older than HOUSEKEEPING_INTERVAL_S (currently not enforced — it always runs).
A frozen repo (no new commits, no ticket changes, no new branches) gains nothing
from a full housekeeping run.

## Solution

Extend `housekeeping_needed()` to also check:
1. Any commits since last housekeeping commit? (`git log <last-hk>..HEAD --oneline`)
2. Any tickets modified since last housekeeping? (`git diff --name-only <last-hk> HEAD -- tickets/`)
3. Any new/deleted local branches since last housekeeping?

If all three are empty → skip housekeeping, log "housekeeping: skipped (no changes)".

## Acceptance criteria

- Housekeeping skipped on idle repos (no git activity since last hk commit)
- Still runs at least once per 24h regardless (safety floor)
- Log shows skip reason

## Notes

Risk: misses external changes (remote pushes by other agents). Mitigation: git fetch
is already part of housekeeping_needed check, or run git fetch before the idle check.
